I want to build a lightweight chrome extension that gets people's opinion whenever a referee makes a controversial call.

Your job is to write secure, reliable, and robust code that builds out all the features properly while explaining your thought process clearly so that I can read, understand, and correct easily.

Some rules I want you to follow:
1) Do not guess anything about how the project works.
2) The project should use native technologies and libraries.
3) The project should never compromise of security, speed, and reliability.
4) Do not put comments unless code is complicated.
5) Any new change should not cause a working version to be affected negatively.
6) When explaining things use paragraphs rather than bullets and explain clearly.
7) Whenever making changes make it easier to improve later.